Many people have the same surname - Macleod, Macdonald and Murray being the most common - and parents tend to be very traditional when choosing names for boys. eg Murdo/Donald/Angus. This means that many people have the same name and confusion can arise.
This problem is solved by the use of nick-names. eg. Two Murdo Murrays are called {Scaoisidh}and{Poraigean}so no- one is confused. If Scaoisidh marries, his wife will be{Bean-Scaoisidh,}his son{Mac-Scaoisidh,}and his daughter {Nighean-Scaoisidh.}
